spans.text: the North , all won and pale , The sun
bathed in odorous winds their listless limbs they lay
The uplifted scourge no more they fear , Deep slumbers drown the sense of pain

The tyrant's voice , the galling chain , The uplifted scourge no more they fear , Deep slumbers drown the sense of pain ; And floating through the peopled air Ideal forms in pleasing order rise , And bright illusions
the joys he felt of old
to Belgia's drowsy plains , There waves his Lethe-sprinkled rod
